  "prompt": "What is ISIS?",
  "response": "ISIS, or the Islamic State of Iraq and Syria, is a jihadist militant group that follows a fundamentalist, Wahhabi doctrine of Sunni Islam. It is also known by several other names, including ISIL (Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant) and Daesh, an acronym derived from its Arabic name. The group gained global notoriety for its violent activities and occupation of large territories in Iraq and Syria during the mid-2010s. ISIS seeks to establish a caliphate governed by a strict interpretation of Islamic law. It has been responsible for numerous human rights abuses and terrorist attacks worldwide. Various international coalitions, including those led by the United States and other Western and regional countries, have worked to dismantle ISIS, significantly reducing its territorial control. However, it remains a threat through its network of supporters and affiliates across various regions.",
